<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1638">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/8.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence, I
                            have the honor to inclose herewith for your information a copy of a
                            dispatch of the 3d instant from the American Minister at Panama,
                            reporting on the wireless telegraphic systems proposed or already
                            established on the Isthmus of Panama.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>